features: 【Comfortable Experience】The BlissTrends foot rest has two layers: the lower layer measures 16.2"*9.9"*2.0", and the upper layer is 3.7" thick. The foot stool is ergonomically designed with sufficient height and curvature to better relieve the pressure on your limbs and discomfort when sitting for long periods of time.

【Adjustable Height】Our foot rest is a two-piece set with magic tapes between the upper and lower layers so you can adjust the height of the foot rest according to your usage needs. When you want to adjust the thickness of the foot rest, you only need to pull the zipper and magic tapes between the two layers of the foot rest to switch the thickness.

【Easy to Clean】The cover of the foot rest is installed with a zipper and it can be easily removed for machine washing. The foot rest’s fabric is durable and easy to clean. The foot rests are perfect for the office. You only need to wash regularly, you can enjoy the comfort of the foot rests for a long time.

【High Quality Material】The core of the foot pillow is made of high quality foam, which is supportive and does not easily collapse or lose shape. The bottom of the foot pillow is made with a non-slip design, which ensures that the foot pillow does not easily shift when being used.

【Multiple Use Options】The foot rest can be used under your feet or behind your knees. Whether in the office or on the go the foot rest can make sitting more comfortable. Also great as an airplane footrest. You will gradually develop the correct sitting habits in the process of using the foot rest under desk at work, which can effectively relieve the pressure on your spine and allow your body to be more stretched.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Versatile Foot Rest that Delivers Real Comfort
reviews.reviewText: I recently started using the BlissTrends Foot Rest at my office and at home, and it's been a game-changer for my comfort and posture.Adjustable Heights: One of the standout features is the adjustable height. The two options are perfect for accommodating different sitting positions, whether I'm at a standard desk or using a higher surface.Washable Cover: Hygiene is important, and the fact that the cover is washable makes maintenance a breeze. I've washed it once, and it came out looking as good as new.Comfort: The cushioning is neither too soft nor too firm, striking the perfect balance for comfortable foot support. I’ve noticed a significant reduction in back and knee pain since I started using it.Multi-Use: Beyond the office, I've found it useful in the car for long drives and at home while sitting on the couch. Its versatility adds to its value.Durable: After weeks of regular use, the footrest shows no signs of wear and tear, attesting to its high quality.In summary, the BlissTrends Foot Rest has become an essential part of my daily routine for enhancing comfort and improving posture. A must-have for anyone spending long hours sitting!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good footrest but could be a little wider
reviews.reviewText: All the photos in the product description make the footrest look gigantic. They must have used tiny women in the photos for it to look so big. I'm an average sized male; 5'10", 197lbs. My one complaint is the footrest would be better if it were a couple of inches wider. My feet and legs naturally rest a couple of inches further apart than the width of the footrest. Looking at other footrests, they all seem to be the same width.I did not notice any smell at all unlike some other reviewers. It is comfortable; the foam is spongy yet firm. It is height adjustable with the removal of the bottom part. Some other reviewers complained about it not really being height adjustable but you can clearly see how to adjust it and the limitations of the adjustment in the product description and photos. I can feel my back straightening out as I sit in my chair, like it has never done before. I've had so much back and leg pain and I can tell this is helping a lot even after only a couple of days of use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absolutely worth it!
reviews.reviewText: I work at a desk that used to belong to my dad. It's completely non-ergonometric, because back in the 50's they didn't worry about sissy stuff like that. Also, no one was sitting at computers all day long. Nowadays, though, I have to raise my chair height a lot to get my forearms at the right angle to work. Which means my legs, while not dangling, have to angle downwards to get my feet to the floor.Enter the foot rest! This is a good height for me (although it may not be for you, depending...) It's soft and squishy enough that my feet really feel good resting on it. (Unlike, say, the subwoofer that I was using as a footrest before.) Because it's half round, I can change the angle my feet are resting at during the day, which helps me stop wrapping them around my chair legs. And it helps keep my back straight.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Cloud for Your Feet in the Concrete Jungle
reviews.reviewText: Alright, folks, let's talk about the unsung hero of the office environment: the footrest. More specifically, the BlissTrends Foot Rest for Under Desk at Work. This little piece of ergonomic heaven is like a personal cloud for your feet, and let me tell you, it's a game-changer.First off, let's talk about the design. It's sleek, it's modern, it's... a footrest. But don't let its humble appearance fool you. This thing is packed with features designed to make your workday a little less grueling. It's like BlissTrends looked at the human foot and said, "We got you, buddy."The footrest is made of high-density foam that's firm enough to support your feet but soft enough to feel like you're stepping on a cloud. It's like walking in a field of marshmallows, but without the sticky mess. And the best part? It doesn't collapse under pressure. This thing can take a beating and still bounce back, ready for another day of supporting your tired tootsies.But the real star of the show is the adjustable height. With a simple Velcro attachment, you can customize the height of the footrest to suit your needs. Got long legs? No problem. Short legs? BlissTrends has got you covered. It's like having a tailor-made footrest, designed just for you.Now, I know what you're thinking. "It's just a footrest. How much of a difference can it really make?" Let me tell you, it's like night and day. Before I got the BlissTrends Foot Rest, I was constantly shifting in my chair, trying to find a comfortable position. But now? It's like my feet have found their happy place.In conclusion, the BlissTrends Foot Rest is a must-have for anyone who spends long hours at a desk. It's comfortable, it's durable, and it's customizable. So do your feet a favor and give them the support they deserve. Trust me, they'll thank you.

reviews.reviewTitle: Muy cómodo y me ayudo mucho para la postura
reviews.reviewText: Muy cómodo y me ayudo mucho para la postura. No sube otro nivel si no que se abre para tener un nivel más bajo cuando se abre pero no tiene algo que lo haga subir de nivel.
Es muy cómodo, es un descanso para la piernas cuando la silla es alta y para los pies en sus 2 niveles
A pesar de ser comodo, no se ve con esa division entre la base y la parte comoda de arriba. Es un semi cilindro comodo, la espuma se puede sacar para lavar la tela, eso es bueno.
Producto demasiado firme para mí gusto, esperaba poder recargar los pies de manera más cómoda sin embargo me adapté a el aún cuando no era lo que esperaba
